{
  "doc_id": "24735",
  "text": "Based on prior work and parallel to larger societal divisions in sexual behavior and values [CITATION_1] we expected to observe two large strata, reflecting (1) low and (2) moderate endorsement of sex and drugs, and (3) a smaller strata with high endorsement of sex and drug use. We hypothesized that the three behavioral strata would reflect traditional, moderate, and highly positive (i.e., recreational) sex and drug use norms, respectively. Further, we hypothesized that condom norms would be strong only among groups moderate on the recreation norm scale. That is, traditional groups would not use condoms because, in general, they are more sex negative, while the highly positive sex groups might view condoms as counter to their focus on recreation and pleasure.",
